# Cloudflare Pages security headers.
#
# This app is a static export (output: 'export'), so Next.js `headers()` config
# does NOT apply — security headers must be delivered by the host. Cloudflare
# Pages reads this `_headers` file from the deploy root (Next copies public/* to
# out/), the same way it reads the existing `_redirects` file.
#
# ── Threat being mitigated ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth tokens live in localStorage (see doc/AUTH_TOKEN_SECURITY_HANDOFF.md), so
# the dominant risk is XSS: any injected script could read the token. A strict
# Content-Security-Policy is the single biggest lever against that, alongside
# clickjacking / MIME-sniffing / referrer hardening below.
#
# ── Allowlist provenance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The CSP source lists were derived from an audit of every external origin the
# app contacts at runtime:
#   • https://akunuba-backend.onrender.com  — FastAPI backend (all API calls)
#   • https://*.withpersona.com             — Persona KYC (embedded iframe + SDK)
#   • https://images.unsplash.com           — marketplace placeholder images
#   • https://js.stripe.com                 — Stripe.js (Elements/CardElement iframe + SDK)
#   • https://api.stripe.com                — Stripe API calls made by Stripe.js itself
#   • https://static.cloudflareinsights.com — Cloudflare Web Analytics beacon script
#                                             (auto-injected by Cloudflare Pages; OBS-01)
#   • https://cloudflareinsights.com        — RUM endpoint the beacon POSTs to
#   • https://cdn.plaid.com                 — Plaid Link SDK (script + Link iframe)
#   • https://production.plaid.com / https://sandbox.plaid.com — Plaid API calls
#                                             made by the Link SDK on the host page
#   • wss://akunuba-backend.onrender.com    — realtime WebSockets (notifications/chat).
#                                             CSP scheme matching does NOT let an https:
#                                             source authorize wss: — it must be explicit.
# Google OAuth and social share links are top-level NAVIGATIONS (not embedded
# resources), so they need no CSP allowance. The many `www.w3.org` references in
# the code are SVG xmlns namespaces, not network requests.
#
# ⚠️ Stripe.js also makes secondary calls (fraud-detection telemetry to
# m.stripe.com/r.stripe.com/merchant-ui-api.stripe.com, and an hCaptcha
# challenge under *.hcaptcha.com) that are NOT allowlisted here yet — they
# were observed in local testing but not confirmed necessary for the core
# card-entry flow to work. If a CSP violation for one of these appears in
# production after this fix (browser console), add it to connect-src /
# script-src following the same pattern as the entries above.
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT — keep these in sync:
#   • If you change the backend (NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL), update connect-src.
#   • script-src/style-src use 'unsafe-inline' because Next's static export emits
#     inline hydration scripts and the UI sets inline styles (Tailwind / Framer /
#     GSAP). A strict nonce/hash CSP is not achievable with static export (no
#     server to inject per-request nonces). This CSP therefore hardens resource
#     LOADING and framing; it does not fully neutralize inline-script XSS. The
#     httpOnly-cookie migration in the handoff doc is what closes that gap.
#   • Before trusting this in prod, deploy once and watch the browser console for
#     CSP violations (especially the Persona KYC flow + login). If something is
#     blocked, switch the header name to `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only`
#     temporarily, fix the allowlist, then switch back to enforcing.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://*.withpersona.com https://js.stripe.com https://static.cloudflareinsights.com https://cdn.plaid.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://akunuba-backend.onrender.com wss://akunuba-backend.onrender.com https://*.withpersona.com https://api.stripe.com https://cloudflareinsights.com https://cdn.plaid.com https://production.plaid.com https://sandbox.plaid.com; frame-src 'self' https://*.withpersona.com https://js.stripe.com https://cdn.plaid.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
